<br>
SCM is good, but MC1 is easily as valuable, probably moreso.  MC2 is debatable, depending on your mana regen from other factors.  Only MC3 becomes much less useful.<br>
<br>
LilWolf:<br>
<br>
You mentioned Dire Charm, and also referenced enchanters.  Two points:  Enchanters can use Dire Charm in every zone of the game, Druids are limited to animals, so it is much less useful.  Second, if committed to soloing (which you reference), Enchanters really have no other choice at 60 but to charm solo.  Druids can root/dot, quad, or even porcupine to solo, and I don't think charm soloing is that much quicker for a druid compared to quadding, esp. if you have a Lumi and FoK.  I think that's the main reason more druids are not that eager to get DC.<br>
<br>
Two other minor reasons:  Many mobs that are obvioulsly animals are not flagged so by Verant, and many soloing druids do root/dot or quad, and just haven't played with charming all that much.  Compare that to enchanters, who play around with their charm spells much more frequently.<br>
<br>
Tat <p>Tatanka WolfDancer, 58th Druid<BR>
