<A HREF=http://www.soldiers-of-light.net/>Soldiers of Light</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhaggle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haggle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/5/02 2:09:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26950.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> AA points</span><hr size=1> <br>
I have I guess 31 AA points so far this is what I spent mine on:<br>
<br>
3 innate run speed(the best 3 points  youll EVER spend)<br>
3 regen<br>
MC1<br>
SCM1<br>
MC2<br>
Healing Crit thingy 1(this is kinda cool)<br>
Increased buff duration(want more of this-combine this with natures recovery and you get REALLY solid healing efficiency in some situations)<br>
Dire charm<br>
have 5&amp;1/2 saved need just 1/2 more for insta evac<br>
<br>
There is no way I would change my first 6 points I think that without a doubt run speed and regen are by far the most useful skills for every class out there and many will agree.  My wis isnt topped out although my gear is decent I get around 245 wis with KEI but even still 10 more wis is only 60 more mana and eventually I will cap out so for most its not worth spending it on.   As for skills I think in hindsight the way to go is this for the first 12:  MC1, SC1, SC2, MC2 then into class skills.   That set of arch skill point spending will give you the most mana savings/mana regen over time than any other class skill combo.   MGB I thought I would want but after my guild got a few clerics with it I get very few potg requests anymore so its not worth it.  Dire charm is FUUNN.  Its much better of a class skill for necros and enchanters precisely for the reasons others have mentioned, namely that for enchanters thats really there only viable solo option and for necros it allows them to get pets FAR superior to the ones they can summon in many of hte places they want to hunt.  Also VERY importnatly both those classes can fear and both enchanters and necros can slow.   HOWEVER as a grouping tool in select zones Dire charm is REALLY cool, especially for duoing with another dire charm capable class in already good xp zones like the grey, chardok, solb, etc.  If I'm grouped in the grey and have either a melee to tank so my pet wont get molested, someone who can slow, someone who can fear, or really basically anyone outside of just me then I will pet up and I get faster kills this way.  For chardok, its the same way.  A group of myself, 60 enchanter with dire charm, and a 60 monk easily handled the bridgekeeper area in chardok including the names and just flew through stuff.   Yes its limited due to the number of zones it can be used in but in those zones its VERY useful and more importantly its really an added fun factor for me.  I find myself dragging people out to chardok and the grey just so I can pet up HEHE.   I raid quite abit and possibly a more efficient spending of points would have been to max out SCM and avoided class skills altogether but for now I'm having lots of fun with it and don't regret it at all.   If you have ES legs and can free heal your pet better you can even use it as a more viable solo tactic.  I've seen druids with dark blue wurm pets in the grey solo tank rockfiends using ES leg healing so it can be done and is pretty enjoyable.<br>
<br>
Hierophant Hagglethorn Happyfeet<br>
Nameless Order, Prexus <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=26950.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=26950.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26950.topic&index=25><img src=http://www.execpc.com/~msippel/thedruidsgrove/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=26950.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.threadControl?topicID=26950.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26950.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26950.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm27">General - DAOC<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm29">The Druids Circle<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm18">FAQ & Index